-- CTC Media’s TV Audience Drops Less Than Peers’, TNS-Global Says
-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 2012-08-16T19:11:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-16/ctc-media-s-tv-audience-drops-less-than-peers-tns-global-says.html
CTC Media Inc. (CTCM) ’s CTC television
channel saw its average daily share of Russian viewers decline
less than competitors’ in the week to Aug. 12, data researcher
TNS-Global said.  Share of Russian viewers aged 18 years and older for CTC
TV, the Nasdaq-listed Russian media company’s biggest source of
revenue, fell to 4.8 percent in the week to Aug. 12 from 5
percent a week earlier, TNS-Global said by e-mail today. CTC
rose to seventh most-watched TV channel in the week to Aug. 12,
as REN TV’s  share of viewers slid to 4.5 percent from 5.1
percent a week earlier.  CTC’s average daily audience among viewers 4 years old and
over dropped to 5.2 percent in the week to Aug. 12 from 5.4
percent in the previous week, the data show. CTC rose to sixth-
most watched TV channel from seventh last week, outpacing Fifth
Channel, the researcher said.  Russia’s NTV Television, Rossiya-1 and Pervyi Kanal were
the top three most watched channels in both categories.
Rossiya-2 and TNT TV placed ahead of CTC among viewers 4 years
and older, the data show. Rossiya-2, TNT TV, Fifth Channel
outpaced CTC among viewers 18 years and older in the week to
Aug. 12, the data showed.  To contact the reporters on this story:
